 uncoated tablet contains: Betamethasone Sodium Phosphate I.P. equivalent to Betamethasone 0.5 mg','1','04:16 PM') , ('90','556','BETNESOL ORAL DROP','BETNESOLORALDROP','15ML','12/24','NA147','491.000','0','0','18.29','25.6','19.56298','23.58209','16.46','716','55','GLAXO','GLAXO','G1','N','Y','','2011-06-30','0','12.00','','0','0','4.5','medicine_images/b_med/b_med050.png','medicine_images/b_med/b_med150.png','medicine_images/b_med/b_med250.png','medicine_images/b_med/b_med350.png','Betamethasone (0.5mg)','Betnesol Oral Drops is a steroid It is used in the treatment of inflammation severe allergies flare ups of ongoing illnesses It is also used to treat many other medical problems that require either reduction of inflammation or suppression of the immune system br br Betnesol Oral Drops may be taken with or without food It should be taken exactly as prescribed by your doctor Your doctor will decide the dose and how often you should take them You should take this medicine regularly to get the most benefit from it Do not stop taking the medicine even if you feel better unless the doctor tells you so br br Using of the medicine may cause few common side effects such as a reduction in bone density and an upset stomach Let your doctor know if any of these side effects bother you If this medicine is used for a long time you may have to get regular tests to check your bone density br br Before using this medicine inform your doctor if you are allergic to any medicine or have liver problems This medicine is not recommended during pregnancy Pregnant and breastfeeding mothers should consult with their doctors before using the medicine ','1','04:16 PM') , ('92','5562','BETNESOL FORTE TAB','BETNESOLFORTETAB','20`S','06/25','6L3B','1588.000','0','0','18.36','25.7','19.63786','23.58811','16.52','716','55','GLAXO','GLAXO','G1','N','N','','2011-06-30','0','12.00','','0','0','4.5','medicine_images/b_med/b_med021.png','medicine_images/b_med/b_med121.png','medicine_images/b_med/b_med