','','0','0','4.5','medicine_images/a_med/a_med0113.png','medicine_images/a_med/a_med1113.png','medicine_images/a_med/a_med2113.png','medicine_images/a_med/a_med3113.png','Levosalbutamol (50mcg) + Beclometasone (50mcg)','Aerocort Inhaler is used in the treatment of asthma wheezing and shortness of breath It relaxes the muscles of the air passages and makes it easier to breathe br br Your doctor will tell you how often you need to use your inhaler It s important that you take the lowest dose needed to effectively control your asthma The effect of this medicine may be noticeable after a few days but will only reach its maximum after a few weeks This medicine must be used regularly to be effective so go on taking it even if you don t have any symptoms That means it s doing its job If you stop taking it your asthma may get worse It should not be used to relieve sudden asthma attacks If an asthma attack occurs use your quick relief inhaler reliever To get the benefit from this medicine you need to make sure you get your inhaler technique right otherwise it does not work as well br br The most common side effects are hoarseness of voice sore throat fungal infection of mouth respiratory tract infection headache and muscle cramp If you get these don t stop taking it but do talk to your doctor You can help prevent some of these symptoms by rinsing your mouth and throat with water or brushing your teeth after using your inhaler There are other rarer side effects which can be serious Talk to your doctor if you re worried about them In general you should be trying to avoid situations that make your asthma worse your triggers and try not to smoke br br Ask your doctor whether it s safe to take this medicine if you re pregnant or breastfeeding Before taking it you should tell your doctor if you have any kidney or liver diseases so that your doctor can prescribe a suitable dose for you ','1','09:54 PM') , ('223','32006745','.ASTHALIN  - 2*','.ASTHALIN2','30`S','','','0.000','0','0','0','0','0','NaN','0','725','66','CIPLA LT','CIPLA LTD.','R26','Y','Y','','2011-06-30','0','12.00','','0','0','4.5','uploads/manage_medicine_image/photo/resize/ASTHALIN__-_2.jpg','uploads/manage_medicine_image/photo/resize/ASTHALIN__-_2_2.jpg','','','Salbutamol 2 mg.','Composition: Each uncoated tablet contains Salbutamol Sulphate IP equivalent to Salbutamol 2 mg.','0','09:54 PM') , ('224','32006895','CIPLAR - 40*','CIPLAR40','15`S','11/25','SB30079','158.000','0','0','34.44','48.21','36.83702','23.5905','30.99','725','66','CIPLA LT','CIPLA LTD.','R20','N','Y','','2011-06-30','0','12.00','','0','0','4.5','uploads/manage_medicine_image/photo/resize/CIPLAR_-_40.jpg','uploads/manage_medicine_image/photo/resize/CIPLAR_-_40_2.jpg','','','Propranolol 40 mg','CIPLAR 40MG contains Propranolol which belongs to a group of medicines called beta-blockers, which have effects on the heart and circulation of the body. It is used to treat hypertension, angina, arrythmias (disorders of heart rhythm), migraine and proliferating infantile hemangioma','1','09:54 PM') , ('225','32006746','ASTHALIN  - 4 *','ASTHALIN4','30`S','','','0.000','0','0','0','0','0','NaN','0','725','66','CIPLA LT','CIPLA LTD.','R26','N','Y','','2011-06-30','0','12.00','','0','0','4.5','medicine_images/a_med/a_med075.png','medicine_images/a_med/a_med175.png','medicine_images/a_med/a_med275.png','medicine_images/a_med/a_med375.png','Salbutamol (4mg)','Asthalin 4 Tablet is used to relieve symptoms of asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary disease COPD such as coughing wheezing and breathlessness It helps in relaxing the muscles of the air passages thus widening it and making it easier to breathe br br You can take Asthalin 4 Tablet with or without food The dose will depend on your condition and how you respond to the medicine Try to take it at the same time each day It is important to keep taking this medicine until your doctor tells you not to Use this medicine regularly to get the most benefit from it even if you feel well br br This medicine is generally safe and effective but some common side effects include tremor headache fast heart rate and muscle cramps These side effects are not often dangerous and they should gradually improve as your body gets used to this medicine There are other rarer side effects and you should call your doctor straight away if you get chest pain a very bad headache or very bad dizziness br br Before using this medicine you should tell your doctor if you have high blood pressure an overactive thyroid gland a history of heart problems diabetes or low levels of potassium in your blood to make sure it is safe Also make sure your doctor knows if you are pregnant or breastfeeding before taking this medicine This medicine can make you feel dizzy or shaky so avoid driving cycling or using tools or machinery until you feel better You should not smoke as it causes damage to your lungs and will make your condition worse ','1','09:54 PM') , ('226','32006753','.ASTHALIN SA-8','.ASTHALINSA8','10`S','','','0.000','0','0','0','0','0','NaN','0','725','66','CIPLA LT','CIPLA LTD.','R26','N','N','','2011-06-30','0','12.00','','0','0','4.5','','','','','','','0','09:54 PM') , ('227','32006754','ASTHALIN SYRUP*','ASTHALINSYRUP','100ML','07/25','R830613','3476.000','0','0','13.6','19.04','14.54656','23.6','12.24','725','66','CIPLA LT','CIPLA LTD.','R26','Y','Y','','2011-06-30','0','12.00','','0','0','4.5','medicine_images/a_med/a_med040.png','medicine_images/a_med/a_med140.png','medicine_images/a_med/a_med040.png','medicine_images/a_med/a_med140.png','Salbutamol (2mg/5ml)','Asthalin Syrup is used to relieve symptoms of asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary disease COPD such as coughing wheezing and breathlessness It helps in relaxing the muscles of the air passages thus widening it and making it easier to breathe br br You can take Asthalin Syrup with or without food The dose will depend on your condition and how you respond to the medicine Try to take it at the same time each day It is important to keep taking this medicine until your doctor tells you not to Use this medicine regularly to get the most benefit from it even if you feel well br br This medicine is generally safe and effective but some common side effects include tremor headache fast heart rate and muscle cramps These side effects are not often dangerous and they should gradually improve as your body gets used to this medicine There are other rarer side effects and you should call your doctor straight away if you get chest pain a very bad headache or very bad dizziness br br Before using this medicine you should tell your doctor if you have high blood pressure an overactive thyroid gland a history of heart problems diabetes or low levels of potassium in your blood to make sure it is safe Also make sure your doctor knows if you are pregnant or breastfeeding before taking this medicine This medicine can make you feel dizzy or shaky so avoid driving cycling or using tools or machinery until you feel better You should not smoke as it causes damage to your lungs and will make your condition worse ','1','09:54 PM') , ('228','32006750','ASTHALIN RESP SOL.*','ASTHALINRESPSOL','15ML','07/25','R530374','383.000','0','0','8.16','11.42','8.727936','23.57324','7.34','725','66','CIPLA LT','CIPLA LTD.','R15','N','Y','','2011-06-30','0','12.00','','0','0','4.5','medicine_images/a_med/a_med0511.png','medicine_images/a_med/a_med1511.png','medicine_images/a_med/a_med2511.png','medicine_images/a_med/a_med3511.png','Salbutamol (5mg)','Asthalin Respirator Solution belongs to a group of medicines called fast acting bronchodilators or relievers It s used to treat the symptoms of asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary disease COPD such as coughing wheezing and breathlessness br br Asthalin Respirator Solution is called reliever inhalers because they give you quick relief from breathing problems when you need it In most cases you will be given another inhaler to prevent your symptoms a preventer and you should use this regularly every day Asthalin Respirator Solution works quickly and the effects can last several hours You can take it at any time of day but only use it when you notice symptoms such as coughing wheezing shortness of breath tightness in the chest or you know that you are going to do an activity that can cause breathlessness When an asthma attack happens you should take the number of puffs your doctor recommends There are several types of inhaler devices so make sure you know how to use your inhaler correctly otherwise it may not work Do not stop using this medicine unless your doctor tells you to If you stop your breathing problems could get worse br br Asthalin Respirator Solution is generally safe and effective but may cause some common side effects which include feeling a bit shaky changes to your heart rate headaches and muscle cramps These side effects are not often dangerous and should gradually improve as your body gets used to this medicine There are other rare side effects and you should call your doctor straight away if you get chest pain a very bad headache or very bad dizziness br br Before using Asthalin Respirator Solution you should tell your doctor if you have high blood pressure an overactive thyroid gland a history of heart problems diabetes or low levels of potassium in your blood to make sure it is safe Also make sure your doctor knows if you are pregnant or breast feeding before taking this medicine This medicine can make you feel dizzy or shaky therefore do not drive use tools or machinery until you feel better Avoid smoking as it causes damage to your lungs and will make your condition worse ','1','09:54 PM') , ('229','32006744','.ASTHALIN ROTACAPS','.ASTHALINROTACAPS','30`S','','','0.000','0','0','0','0','0','NaN','0','725','66','CIPLA LT','CIPLA LTD.','R15','Y','Y','','2011-06-30','0','12.00','','0','0','4.5','','','','','','','0','09:54 PM') , ('230','42244','ZOCON TRANSGEL','ZOCONTRANSGEL','15GM','',