New Asthalin Expectorant is taken in a dose and duration as advised by the doctor. The dose you are given will depend on your condition and how you respond to the medicine. You should keep taking this medicine for as long as your doctor recommends. If you stop treatment too early your symptoms may come back and your condition may worsen. Let your doctor know about all other medications you are taking as some may affect, or be affected by this medicine.
','1','09:54 PM') , ('239','32006802','BECLATE-200 INH.','BECLATE200INH','200MD','05/26','BA31489','63.000','0','0','429.81','601.74','459.7248','23.60076','386.83','725','66','CIPLA LT','CIPLA LTD.','R17','N','N','','2011-06-30','0','12.00','','0','0','4.5','uploads/manage_medicine_image/photo/resize/BECLATE-200_INH.jpg','uploads/manage_medicine_image/photo/resize/BECLATE-200_INH2.jpg','','','Beclomethasone Dipropionate IP 200 mcg. Propellant 134','Composition: Each actuation delivers Beclomethasone Dipropionate IP 200 mcg. Propellant 134a q.s. Absolute alcohol 14.44% v/v.','1','09:54 PM') , ('242','32006892','CIPLACTIN TABS','CIPLACTINTABS','15`S','07/25','BA31970','252.000','9','1','42.37','59.32','45.31895','23.60258','38.13','725','66','CIPLA LT','CIPLA LTD.','R26','Y','Y','','2011-06-30','0','12.00','','11.11111','0','4.5','medicine_images/c_med/c_med0106.png','medicine_images/c_med/c_med1106.png','medicine_images/c_med/c_med2106.png','medicine_images/c_med/c_med3106.png','Cyproheptadine (4mg)','Ciplactin Tablet belongs to a group of medicines called antihistamines It is used in the treatment of various allergic conditions It relieves symptoms like itching swelling and rashes It is also used to treat loss of appetite need for food It is an effective hunger stimulant br br Ciplactin Tablet can be taken with or without food and it is better to take it in a dose and duration as advised by the doctor You may need this medicine only on days you have symptoms or you may need to take it every day to prevent symptoms from happening If you stop taking it earlier than advised your symptoms may come back This medicine is generally very safe br br This medicine may cause some amount of dizziness so do not drive or do anything that needs attention Consult your doctor if it persists or worry you It may cause headache or increase appetite in some cases Before taking it you should tell your doctor if you have any problems with your liver or kidneys or with your heart br br Pregnant or breastfeeding women should also consult with their doctor before taking it Avoid drinking alcohol as it can cause excessive drowsiness with this medicine ','1','09:54 PM') , ('243','6631','.CIPLACTIN SYP.','.CIPLACTINSYP','100ML','','','0.000','0','0','0','0','0','NaN','0','725','66','CIPLA LT','CIPLA LTD.','R29','N','Y','','2011-06-30','0','0.00','','0','0','4.5','medicine_images/c_med/c_med0160.png','medicine_images/c_med/c_med1160.png','medicine_images/c_med/c_med2160.png','medicine_images/c_med/c_med3160.png','Diclofenac (50mg) + Serratiopeptidase (10mg)','Cipzen D Tablet is a combination of two medicines It is used to reduce pain and inflammation in conditions like rheumatoid arthritis ankylosing spondylitis and osteoarthritis It is also used to relieve muscle pain back pain toothache or pain in the ear and throat br br Cipzen D Tablet can be taken with or without food The dose will depend on what you are taking it for and how well it helps your symptoms You should take it as advised by your doctor Do not take more or use it for a longer duration than recommended by the doctor br br The most common side effects of this medicine include nausea vomiting heartburn stomach pain indigestion diarrhea and loss of appetite If any of these side effects bother you or get worse you should speak to your doctor Your doctor may be able to suggest ways of preventing or reducing the side effects br br Before taking it you should let your doctor know if you have a history of ulcer or bleeding in your stomach high blood pressure or have any trouble with your heart kidneys or liver Let your doctor also know about all the other medicines you are taking because they may affect or be affected by this medicine br br Pregnant or breastfeeding women should consult their doctor before starting treatment You should also avoid drinking alcohol while you are taking this medicine as alcohol can cause excessive drowsiness ','0','09:54 PM') , ('244','32006894','CIPLAR -10*','CIPLAR10','15`S','08/26','SB31009','765.000','0','0','15.71','22','16.80342','23.62084','14.14','725','66','CIPLA LT','CIPLA LTD.','R20','N','Y','','2011-06-30','0','12.00','','0','0','4.5','uploads/manage_medicine_image/photo/resize/CIPLAR_-10.jpg','uploads/manage_medicine_image/photo/resize/CIPLAR_-10_2.jpg','','','Propranolol 10 mg','Composition: Each uncoated tablet contains: Propranolol Hydrochloride IP 10 mg','1','09:54 PM') , ('245','97275','NEBI - 5','NEBI5','10`S','03/25','SPD230612','352.000','0','0','75','105','80.22','23.6','67.5','2118','20','ARISTO P','ARISTO PHARMACEUTICALS PVT.LTD','AR3','N','N','','2011-06-30','0','12.00','','0','0','4.5','','','','','','','1','09:54 PM') , ('247','32006904','CIPLOX - 250 *','CIPLOX250','10`S','06/26','SB30734','163.000','13','1','17.51','24.52','18.72869','23.6187','15.76','725','66','CIPLA LT','CIPLA LTD.','R26','N','Y','','2011-06-30','0','12.00','','7.692307','0','4.5','uploads/manage_medicine_image/photo/resize/ciplox__250.jpg','','','','','CIPLOX 250MG contains Ciprofloxacin which belongs to a group of medicines called fluoroquinolones. It is used to treat infections of the skin, sinuses, bone, lung, ear, abdomen, kidney, prostate, and bladder (bacterial infections). It may also used in the management of patients with low white blood cell counts (neutropenia) who have a fever that is suspected to be due to a bacterial infection. Take the medicine according to the dose and duration as advised by your doctor.','1','09:54 PM') , ('248','32006905','CIPLOX - 500 *','CIPLOX500','10`S','09/26','SB31079','1056.000','10','1','34','47.6','36.3664','23.59999','30.6','725','66','CIPLA LT','CIPLA LTD.','R26','Y','Y','','2011-06-30','0','12.00','','10','0','4.5','uploads/manage_medicine_image/photo/resize/ciplox_500.jpg','uploads/manage_medicine_image/photo/resize/ciplox_500_2.jpg','uploads/manage_medicine_image/photo/resize/ciplox_500_3.jpg','','','Composition: Each film-coated tablet contains: Ciprofloxacin Hydrochloride IP equivalent to Ciprofloxacin 500 mg.','1','09:54 PM') , ('249','32006911','CIPLOX  - TZ','CIPLOXTZ','10`S','04/26','SB30470','854.000','5','1','122.54','171.55','131.0688','23.59733','110.28','725','66','CIPLA LT','CIPLA LTD.','R26','N','Y','','2011-06-30','0','12.00','','20','0','4.5','uploads/manage_medicine_image/photo/resize/ciplox-tz-1406055557-10001739.jpg','uploads/manage_medicine_image/photo/resize/ciplox-tz-1406055557-100017391.jpg','','','','Ciplox-TZ is a combination medicine containing ciprofloxacin and tinidazole as active ingredients. It works by killing the infection-causing bacteria. The dose, duration and frequency of taking Ciplox-TZ tablets are decided by your doctor. Always take medicine as prescribed by the doctor for the prescribed duration.','1','09:54 PM') , ('250','32013033','DYTOR  - 5','DYTOR5','15`S','06/26','SB30766','1057.000','0','0','51.24','71.73','54.8063','23.59361','46.11','725','66','CIPLA LT','CIPLA LTD.','R14','N','N','','2011-06-30','0','12.00','','0','0','4.5','medicine_images/d_med/d_med032.png','medicine_images/d_med/d_med132.png','medicine_images/d_med/d_med232.png','medicine_images/d_med/d_med332.png','Torasemide (5mg)','Dytor 5 Tablet belongs to a group of medicines called diuretics or water tablets It is used to reduce the swelling edema caused by too much water in the body in people who have heart failure liver disease or kidney disease This medicine is also used to treat high blood pressure br br Dytor 5 Tablet helps your body get rid of extra water and salt through urine It may be used alone or in combination with other medicines as per the dose advised by your doctor It can be taken with or without food and should be taken at the same time each day It is best to avoid taking this medicine within 4 hours of your bedtime to prevent having to get up at night to urinate br br It is important to continue taking this medication even if you feel well If you stop taking it without consulting your doctor your condition may worsen Lifestyle changes like reducing stress restricting salt intake and stopping smoking may help this medication work better br br Common side effects of this medicine include headache dizziness dehydration decreased blood pressure and stomach upset These are usually mild and disappear after a short time Consult your doctor if they bother you or do not go away br br Before taking this medicine let your doctor know if you have any liver problems Pregnant or breastfeeding women should also consult their doctor before taking it Regular monitoring of kidney function tests and electrolyte levels is important while using this medicine It may reduce the potassium level in your blood so your doctor may ask you to add potassium rich foods to your diet such as bananas coconut water etc or prescribe supplements ','1','09:54 PM') , ('251','32006906','CIPLOX - 750','CIPLOX750','10`S','','','0.000','0','0','0','0','0','NaN','0','725','66','CIPLA LT','CIPLA LTD.','R26','N','Y','','2011-06-30','0','12.00','','0','0','4.5','uploads/manage_medicine_image/photo/resize/ciplox_750mg.jpg','','','','','Ciplox 750 MG Tablet can be taken with or without food. For the ease of remembering, take Ciplox 750 MG Tablet around the same time every day. Take Ciplox 750 MG Tablet one-two hours before or after taking antacids as they increase the time taken by this medicine to show its effect. Take Ciplox 750 MG Tablet two hours before/after taking dairy products as they can affect its absorption and decrease its beneficial effects.','1','09:54 PM') , ('254','664','CIPLOX EYE OINT.','CIPLOXEYEOINT','5GM','','','0.000','0','0','0','0','0','NaN','0','725','66','CIPLA LT','CIPLA LTD.','R29','N','Y','','2011-06-30','0','0.00','','0','0','4.5','uploads/manage_medicine_image/photo/resize/IMG_20220617_210212.jpg','uploads/manage_medicine_image/photo/resize/ciplox__onnment.jpeg','uploads/manage_medicine_image/photo/resize/ciplox__onnment.jpeg','uploads/manage_medicine_image/photo/resize/ciplox__onnment.jpeg','','Ciplox Eye Ointment is an antibiotic, used in the treatment of bacterial infections of the eye. It relieves the symptoms of the infection by stopping the further growth of the causative microorganisms.','1','09:54 PM') , ('256','6642','CIPLIN SUSP','CIPLINSUSP','50ML','','','0.000','0','0','0','0','0','NaN','0','725','66','CIPLA LT','CIPLA LTD.','R29','N','Y','','2011-06-30','0','0.00','','0','0','4.5','uploads/manage_medicine_image/photo/resize/default_img108.jpg','','','','','','1','09:54 PM') , ('260','32006988','DANOGEN - 50','DANOGEN50','10`S','02/25','23S2HCA004','20.000','0','0','121.57','170.2','130.0313','23.6009','109.41','725','66','CIPLA LT','CIPLA LTD.','R22','N','N','','2011-06-30','0','12.00','','0','0','4.5','','','','','Serratiopeptidase (10mg)','Danzen Forte 10mg Tablet is used in the treatment of pain and inflammation It helps relieve pain and swelling in postoperative wounds and inflammatory diseases br br Danzen Forte 10mg Tablet can be taken with or without food In general you should try to use the smallest amount necessary to control your symptoms for the shortest possible time You should take this medicine regularly while you need it Try not to miss doses as this will make the medicine less effective br br It is generally safe with little or no side effects However if you experience any symptoms which you think is caused by the medicine you should let your doctor know Your doctor may be able to suggest ways of preventing or reducing the symptoms br br To make it sure it is safe for you before taking this medicine let your doctor know if you have any medical conditions or disorders You should also tell your doctor all the other medicines you are using or taking Pregnant and breastfeeding women should consult their doctors before using this medicine ','1','09:54 PM') , ('261','32006985','DANOGEN -100*','DANOGEN100','10`S','07/25','23S2HCA017','43.000','0','0','249.97','349.96','267.3679','23.60043','224.97','725','66','CIPLA LT','CIPLA LTD.','R22','N','N','','2011-06-30','0','12.00','','0','0','4.5','uploads/manage_medicine_image/photo/resize/DANOGEN_-100.jpg','uploads/manage_medicine_image/photo/resize/DANOGEN_-1001.jpg','','','','Danogen-100 Capsule 10&prime;s belongs to the class of drugs called synthetic steroids used to treat endometriosis and breast cysts. Endometriosis is a disorder in which the tissue lining the uterus (endometrium) grows on the ovaries, bowel, or tissues lining the pelvis. The most common symptom is pelvic pain.','1','09:54 PM') , ('262','32006986','DANOGEN - 200*','DANOGEN200','10`S','05/25','23S2HCA016','182.000','0','0','426.39','596.95','456.0667','23.60051','383.75','725','66','CIPLA LT','CIPLA LTD.','R22','N','N','','2011-06-30','0','12.00','','0','0','4.5','uploads/manage_medicine_image/photo/resize/DANOGEN_-_200.jpg','uploads/manage_medicine_image/photo/resize/DANOGEN_-_2001.jpg','','','','Danogen 200 Capsule 10&prime;s contains Danazol which works by suppressing the activity of ovaries. Thus, it decreases the amount of estrogen in the body and induces temporary menopause. Thereby, it shrinks the tissue outside the uterus or stops its growth. Take Danogen 200 Capsule 10&prime;s as prescribed by your doctor.','1','09:54 PM') , ('263','32007117','FERTOMID-50*','FERTOMID50','10`S','','','0.000','0','0','0','0','0','NaN','0','725','66','CIPLA LT','CIPLA LTD.','R22','N','Y','','2011-06-30','0','12.00','','0','0','4.5','','','','','','','1','09:54 PM') , ('264','87506','METGLAR - 1','METGLAR1','10`S','','','0.000','0','0','0','0','0','NaN','0','766','87','ABBOTT','ABBOTT INDIA LTD.','N4','N','N','','2011-06-30','0','12.00','','0','0','4.5','','','','','','','1','09:54 PM') , ('265','32007116','FERTOMID-25','FERTOMID25','10`S','','','0.000','0','0','0','0','0','NaN','0','725','66','CIPLA LT','CIPLA LTD.','R22','N','Y','','2011-06-30','0','12.00','','0','0','4.5','uploads/manage_medicine_image/photo/resize/FERTOMID-25.jpg','uploads/manage_medicine_image/photo/resize/FERTOMID-25_